Purchase options and add-ons

  • Answer your door from anywhere with Video Doorbell and help protect your home inside and out with our wire-free Outdoor 4 smart security camera.
  • See and speak from the Blink app — Experience 1080p HD live view, infrared night vision, and crisp two-way audio.
  • Two-year battery life — Set up yourself in minutes and get up to two years of power on each device with the included AA lithium batteries and Sync Module 2.
  • Enhanced motion detection with Outdoor 4 — With our all-new Outdoor 4, enjoy a wider field of view and be alerted to motion faster with dual-zone, enhanced motion detection.
  • Save and share clips — Choose to store events in the cloud with a free 30-day trial of the Blink Subscription Plan or locally with the included Sync Module 2 and USB drive (sold separately).
  • Designed for every home — Wire Video Doorbell to sound your existing in-home chime or go wire-free with in-app chime alerts. You can even use Blink Mini (sold separately) as an indoor plug-in chime.
  • Works with Alexa — Connect to an Alexa-enabled device to engage live view, arm and disarm your system, and more using your voice.
  • Includes one Video Doorbell, three Outdoor 4 cameras, one Sync Module 2, eight AA lithium batteries, four mounting kits, one USB cable, and one power adapter.

We want you to know

Blink Video Doorbell is weather resistant with a seal that protects against water. We recommend mounting it to your home with the included back plate by following these instructions.

Save and share unlimited videos for 60-days with an optional Blink Subscription Plan (sold separately). Local storage is available with the Sync Module 2 (requires USB flash drive – sold separately).

Home is in your hands

Whether you're working, walking the dog, or busy making memories — Video Doorbell lets you see who's at your door with helpful features like:

Designed for every home

Created to help make your life safer and easier, Video Doorbell lets you personalize your experience.

Be alerted to what matters

Create customized activity and privacy zones so you only see the movement you care about. Plus, control all your Blink devices from one account so you can monitor your home or business at the same time.

Make an entrance

Video Doorbell comes in two colors so you can select the option that best matches your home decor and aesthetic.

Getting started is easy

Step 1

Sign in to or create an account in the Blink app.

Step 2

Add your device(s) to your account and connect to wifi.

Step 3

Choose to install wire-free or wired to your existing home chime in the app and follow the instructions to complete setup.

From the unexpected to the unforgettable

Record, save, and share videos and clips from your Blink devices with ease.


Blink Subscription Plan

Experience the convenience and added benefits of the Blink Subscription Plan with your included 30-day free trial. Then, choose to subscribe for just $3 per month per device or $10 per month for unlimited Blink devices on an account.

Learn more about the Blink Subscription Plan.

Local Storage: Sync Module 2

Save your clips locally with the included Sync Module 2 for no additional fee. USB flash drive required (sold separately).

Learn more about local storage via Sync Module 2.

Blink Video Doorbell Technical Details

Field of view

135° horizontal, 80° vertical

Video resolution

Record and view in 1080p HD video during the day and with infrared HD night vision after dark.

Photo resolution

View captured images in 640 x 360 nHD

Camera frame rate

Up to 30 fps

Size

130 x 42 x 34 mm

Weight

91 grams

Power

Blink Video Doorbell Power: 2 AA 1.5V lithium metal (non-rechargeable) batteries. Existing chime wiring: 16-24 VAC

Sync Module 2 power: 100-220V AC to 5V DC converter included.

*Battery life of up to two years, based on default settings. Features may vary with configuration and settings. Battery life will vary based on device settings, use, and environmental factors.

Requirements

Always-on high-speed internet connection (such as broadband, fiber, or DSL). Wifi network: 2.4 GHz 802.11b/g/n.

Connection

Battery or wired

Available colors

Black, White

Minimum smartphone requirements

iOS 15.0, Android 9.0, or Fire 9.0

Blink app

Blink Home Monitor

Included in the box

Includes one Video Doorbell, three Outdoor 4 cameras, one Sync Module 2, eight AA lithium batteries, four mounting kits, one USB cable, and one power adapter

Audio

Speaker output and 2-way audio recording.

LEDs

1 LED ring to help you know when it’s active (optional). Flashes in blue, red, and green. Outdoor camera: 1 blue LED to help you know when it's active (optional). 1 red LED when recording in night vision.

Warranty and service

1-year limited warranty and service included. Use of Blink devices is subject to the terms found here.

Support

Click here to see the setup guide.

Generation

1st Generation

Operating temperature

-4 to 113° F

Software Security Updates

This device receives guaranteed software security updates until at least four years after the device is last available for purchase as a new unit on our websites. Learn more about these software security updates.

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

Incredible Bargain: Security Camera That Exceeds Expectations with Top-Notch Performance
I’m honestly amazed at how much I got for the price of this security camera. After using it for a few weeks, it has far exceeded my expectations in terms of both performance and value. If you’re on the hunt for an affordable, reliable security camera that offers excellent features, this one is a steal.The setup took about an hour, mainly because I took my time to choose the ideal placement and get everything properly configured. The instructions were clear, and the process was fairly simple. Once everything was hooked up, the camera easily synced with the app, which has been user-friendly and reliable ever since.The video quality is fantastic—sharp, HD resolution that’s clear even in low-light conditions thanks to impressive night vision. I provided a video of the day and a photo of night vision. The motion detection is fast and accurate, with few false alerts so far as long as you tweak the sensitivity settings. Plus, I can get instant notifications when the camera detects movement, which is incredibly convenient.One of the features that really sets this camera apart is its battery-powered design, which means you can place it anywhere, free from the need for electrical outlets or complex wiring. I was able to install it in several spots around my property without worrying about cords, and it’s been working perfectly without the hassle of outlets or extension cords. The only issue I had was a line-of-sight issue from the hub. I had to play with which room I plugged the hub in to make sure it could speak to every camera. Basically, my fridge was causing signal problems when a line of sight had the fridge in between. The solution was painless just plugged it into different rooms until all cameras had a good connectionThe storage options are also worth noting. While the camera offers cloud storage, I appreciate that it doesn’t lock you into a subscription model. For those who prefer not to pay for cloud storage, you can use a USB drive to store your footage locally. This gives you flexibility and can save you money in the long run if you don’t want the ongoing fees for cloud storage. This is the route I went, my only irk was that the cloud service separates the videos in a more organized way. Where the USB has all cameras listed in one single group by day. So cloud service brings more premium access.The build quality is solid and weatherproof, which makes it ideal for outdoor use. I’ve had it up in rain and wind without any issues, and it continues to perform flawlessly. One camera was tilted by a squirrel but that's more of a "my house" problem than a blink problem.Other handy features include two-way audio, which is perfect for communicating with anyone at your door or even monitoring deliveries, and the app has been reliable for live streaming and playback.All things considered, this camera delivers premium features—like HD video, accurate motion detection, flexible battery placement, and local storage—at a price that’s hard to beat. If you’re looking for an affordable, no-fuss security solution, I highly recommend this one. It offers excellent value and performance, especially if you don’t want to be tied to cloud storage fees.

    5.0 out of 5 stars
    Incredible Bargain: Security Camera That Exceeds Expectations with Top-Notch Performance

    Reviewed in the United States on November 15, 2024
    I’m honestly amazed at how much I got for the price of this security camera. After using it for a few weeks, it has far exceeded my expectations in terms of both performance and value. If you’re on the hunt for an affordable, reliable security camera that offers excellent features, this one is a steal.

    The setup took about an hour, mainly because I took my time to choose the ideal placement and get everything properly configured. The instructions were clear, and the process was fairly simple. Once everything was hooked up, the camera easily synced with the app, which has been user-friendly and reliable ever since.

    The video quality is fantastic—sharp, HD resolution that’s clear even in low-light conditions thanks to impressive night vision. I provided a video of the day and a photo of night vision. The motion detection is fast and accurate, with few false alerts so far as long as you tweak the sensitivity settings. Plus, I can get instant notifications when the camera detects movement, which is incredibly convenient.

    One of the features that really sets this camera apart is its battery-powered design, which means you can place it anywhere, free from the need for electrical outlets or complex wiring. I was able to install it in several spots around my property without worrying about cords, and it’s been working perfectly without the hassle of outlets or extension cords. The only issue I had was a line-of-sight issue from the hub. I had to play with which room I plugged the hub in to make sure it could speak to every camera. Basically, my fridge was causing signal problems when a line of sight had the fridge in between. The solution was painless just plugged it into different rooms until all cameras had a good connection

    The storage options are also worth noting. While the camera offers cloud storage, I appreciate that it doesn’t lock you into a subscription model. For those who prefer not to pay for cloud storage, you can use a USB drive to store your footage locally. This gives you flexibility and can save you money in the long run if you don’t want the ongoing fees for cloud storage. This is the route I went, my only irk was that the cloud service separates the videos in a more organized way. Where the USB has all cameras listed in one single group by day. So cloud service brings more premium access.

    The build quality is solid and weatherproof, which makes it ideal for outdoor use. I’ve had it up in rain and wind without any issues, and it continues to perform flawlessly. One camera was tilted by a squirrel but that's more of a "my house" problem than a blink problem.

    Other handy features include two-way audio, which is perfect for communicating with anyone at your door or even monitoring deliveries, and the app has been reliable for live streaming and playback.

    All things considered, this camera delivers premium features—like HD video, accurate motion detection, flexible battery placement, and local storage—at a price that’s hard to beat. If you’re looking for an affordable, no-fuss security solution, I highly recommend this one. It offers excellent value and performance, especially if you don’t want to be tied to cloud storage fees.
